The paper focuses on the development of a large-scale dataset for crowd counting and the evaluation of state-of-the-art methods for this task. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The use of Convolutional Neural Networks (CNN) also suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Additionally, the benchmark website and analysis of new problems suggest a focus on information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
